"The brute force approach checks every subarray, which takes O(n²). To optimize it, I use 
Prefix Sum and a HashMap. While traversing the array, I maintain the current prefix sum. At every index,
I look for currentSum - k in the HashMap. If it exists, I add its frequency to my answer because each occurrence
represents a different valid starting point for a subarray
ending at the current index. Finally, I store the current prefix sum by increasing its frequency. This gives an O(n) solution."
